<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id746faa94-2930-11f1-b33a-a9dcf95eef0b" identifier="/us/usc/t17/s1329"><num value="1329">§ 1329.</num><heading> Relation to design patent law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The issuance of a design patent under title 35, United States Code, for an original design for an article of manufacture shall terminate any protection of the original design under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id746faa95-2930-11f1-b33a-a9dcf95eef0b">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/105/304/tV/s502">Pub. L. 105–304, title V, § 502</ref>, <date date="1998-10-28">Oct. 28, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/2916">112 Stat. 2916</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
